                            <comment id="17879853" author="paulk" created="Fri, 6 Sep 2024 12:33:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It is true that md5 is a weak hash for scenarios when there is an attack threat. For it to be an attack threat for GroovyClassLoader, it means that you are allowing someone access to your server/JVM instance. If you are, the hashing algorithm you are using might be the least of your problems.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The downside of sha256 is that it is slightly slower for our usage and only offers minimally reduced collision avoidance. Having said that we might consider swapping to sha256 if we do more performance testing. More likely, we might make the hashing algorithm configurable.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17880107" author="JIRAUSER306847" created="Sun, 8 Sep 2024 08:50:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;i have modify the use of EncodingGroovyMethods.md5 to configure the MD5/SHA-256 algorithm through the environment variable&#160;GROOVY_CACHED_KEY_ALGORITHMS&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
